{
  "stem": "1873.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 295.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But later, when it was known that the people at the destination is dead, and everybody wants to live, they start to hide.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Dig hiding places under the floors and different kinds.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We build a hiding place in the attic of our home.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It so happened that the burgermeister, the mayor of the town, lived-- did live in the same apartment building.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And our apartment was directly connected to the mayor's apartment.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So in the attic, the attic too was connected.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- simple-- cut into the burgermeister's attic, and we made a double wall.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were hidden over there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We entered through our attic to his part, and we camouflaged.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a good hiding place.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You see, Izbica-- for a researcher, Izbica's very well known.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because Izbica was a perfect trap.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Izbica is a town built in a valley.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All around were mountains, hills.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when there was a round-up, it was enough for the [INAUDIBLE] or the Nazis to stay on top of the hills, and they had a perfect view.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no way to escape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also, in the beginning, even in the-- in 1940 already, many people from West Poland-- from the Kolo district, Kolo, from the Poznan district-- were actually resettled to Izbica.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And still later, transports from Czechoslovakia, from Germany, Berlin, Frankfurt, were also, also resettled to Izbica.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Izbica was-- as I said, researchers know about this-- a collection point from where the Jews were later taken to Sobibor, to the death camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as I said, Izbica was about 3,600 Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And very fast in the middle of 1942, the amount dropped.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But soon transport from Slovakia, from Czechoslovakia, went in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again they filled up the capacity-- about 10,000, 15,000 people.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
